abstract: Jermaine Samuels hit the game-winning 3-pointer with 20.5 seconds remaining to lift No. 18 Villanova past No. 1 Kansas 56-55 on Saturday in Philadelphia.

abstract: Hong Kong is gearing up for demonstrations over Christmas week with protesters planning events in districts across the city, including in prime shopping malls, the latest in more than six months of unrest.
snippet: Hong Kong is gearing up for demonstrations over Christmas week with protesters planning events in districts across the city, including in prime shopping malls, the latest in more than six months of unrest.
lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Hong Kong is gearing up for demonstrations over Christmas week with protesters planning events in districts across the city, including in prime shopping malls, the latest in more than six months of unrest.
headline_main: Hong Kong Braces for Protests Over Christmas Holidays
headline_print_headline: Hong Kong Braces for Protests Over Christmas Holidays

abstract: Turkey's parliament approved on Saturday a security and military cooperation deal signed with Libya's internationally recognised government last month, state media reported, an agreement that could pave the way for military help from Ankara.
snippet: Turkey's parliament approved on Saturday a security and military cooperation deal signed with Libya's internationally recognised government last month, state media reported, an agreement that could pave the way for military help from Ankara.
lead_paragraph: ANKARA — Turkey's parliament approved on Saturday a security and military cooperation deal signed with Libya's internationally recognised government last month, state media reported, an agreement that could pave the way for military help from Ankara.
headline_main: Turkey's Parliament Ratifies Security Accord With Libya-Report
headline_print_headline: Turkey's Parliament Ratifies Security Accord With Libya-Report

abstract: The American-born Lady Astor was the first woman to take a seat in the British Parliament. A century later, her legacy is still being debated.
snippet: The American-born Lady Astor was the first woman to take a seat in the British Parliament. A century later, her legacy is still being debated.
lead_paragraph: PLYMOUTH, England — When women finally won the right in 1918 to enter Britain’s Parliament, many expected the first female lawmaker to sit there to come from the ranks of the suffragists, the activists who had fought, often at huge personal cost, for the vote.

abstract: Turkey cannot handle a fresh wave of migrants from Syria, President Tayyip Erdogan said on Sunday, warning that European countries will feel the impact of such an influx if violence in Syria's northwest is not stopped.

abstract: Malik Fitts and Jordan Ford combined to score 31 of their 44 points in the second half and Saint Mary's used a late 12-2 run to beat Nevada 68-63 on Saturday night at the Al Attles Classic.

lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Malik Fitts and Jordan Ford combined to score 31 of their 44 points in the second half and Saint Mary's used a late 12-2 run to beat Nevada 68-63 on Saturday night at the Al Attles Classic.

headline_main: ‘He Accidentally Smashed the Bottle of Wine He Was Opening’

abstract: Meteor showers can light up night skies from dusk to dawn, and if you’re lucky you might be able to catch a glimpse.
snippet: Meteor showers can light up night skies from dusk to dawn, and if you’re lucky you might be able to catch a glimpse.
lead_paragraph: All year long as Earth revolves around the sun, it passes through streams of cosmic debris. The resulting meteor showers can light up night skies from dusk to dawn, and if you’re lucky you might be able to catch a glimpse.
